body:
@changchaishi, in github, it is not working like you described. When you trigger a WF that has workflow_dispatch trigger inside, GH executes the WF file (possibly edited) from the selected branch (the main branch is needed only to declare your WF file). With this approach, you can edit your WF many times to finish your work and make a single squash commit into the master once finished.
Currently, to develop a WF in Gitea, I need to make dozens of commits right into the master and test them until I get what I need. This drastically pollutes the commit history.

@delvh, when a malicious actor has write access to your repo to push changes into your branches, the leakage of secrets becomes less critical.
